President Muhammadu Buhari. (File: AP) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town - United States President Donald Trump is reportedly set to hold a "telephonic meeting" with his Nigerian counterpart President Mohammadu Buhari late on Monday. According to Africa News, Trump was scheduled to speak to Buhari at about 15:45 Nigerian time (09:45 Washington DC time).A journalist with The Globe and Mail, Geoffery York, tweeted and referred to the session as Trump's "Africa Day", as Trump was also expected to speak with South African leader Jacob Zuma.See the tweets below.The telephonic meeting comes as Buhari is currently on vacation in the United Kingdom&nbsp;to "complete and receive results of a series of tests recommended by his doctors".It has been nearly a month since the Nigerian president left his country for the UK.Today is "Africa day" for Donald Trump. He speaks by phone to Nigerian president Buhari at 3:45 pm (Lagos time); then speaks to Jacob Zuma.&mdash; Geoffrey York (@geoffreyyork) February 13, 2017Today is "Africa day" for Donald Trump. He speaks by phone to Nigerian president Buhari at 3:45 pm (Lagos time); then speaks to Jacob Zuma. Trump scheduled to speak by phone to Zuma today at 5:10 pm, after speaking to Buhari first. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.